<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="26" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1390,1726]" pageId="1" pageNumber="26">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,315,1390,1416]" pageId="1" pageNumber="26">Description:</emphasis>
—Annual, small or robust monoecious herbs, 
<quantity box="[902,1042,1390,1416]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.5" metricValueMax="12.0" metricValueMin="5.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="26" unit="cm" value="85.0" valueMax="120.0" valueMin="50.0">50–120 cm</quantity>
high. Stem erect or ascending, glabrous. Leaves deltoid-ovate, lanceolate or ovate-oblong to oval (9–17 × 
<quantity box="[1043,1135,1429,1455]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.0" metricValueMax="9.0" metricValueMin="5.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="26" unit="cm" value="7.0" valueMax="9.0" valueMin="5.0">5–9 cm</quantity>
), without stipule, spirally arranged, apex sub-acute often slightly notched, with a mucro. Flowers unisexual, arranged in small axillary glomerules and the terminal compound inflorescence of agglomerated cymes, male and female flowers intermixed; bracts and bracteoles broadly ovate-spathulate to ovate-lanceolate, apically awned or acute, 1.5–2.0 mm long; tepals 3, ovate-spathulate to ovate-lanceolate, awned or acute, membranous, 3.5–5.0 mm long; stamens 3, 4.5–5.0 mm long; carpels 3, 2.5–3.0 mm long, style short and thick, ovary ovoid, stigmas 3, filiform, with a short beak present in the lower part; fruit circumscissile, ovoid, 1.5–2.0 mm long; seed blackish-brown, shiny, compressed, 
<quantity box="[577,718,1700,1726]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.35" metricValueMax="1.5" metricValueMin="1.2" pageId="1" pageNumber="26" unit="mm" value="1.35" valueMax="1.5" valueMin="1.2">1.2–1.5 mm</quantity>
in diameter.
</paragraph>
